##### Hands-on EC2-00 : How to Connect EC2 instance with SSH.

## Outline

- Part 1 - Launching an Amazon Linux 2 EC2 instance

- Part 2 - Connect with SSH for WINDOWS-"Gitbash"

- Part 3 - Connect with SSH for WINDOWS- "WSL"

- Part 4 - Connect with SSH for MAC and Linux 


## Part 1 - Launching an Amazon Linux 2 EC2 instance

1. Launch an Amazon EC2 instance with name of "First EC2"

To launch an Amazon EC2 instance, you can follow these steps:

**1.1** - **Sign in to the AWS Management Console:**
```text
Go to [AWS Management Console](https://aws.amazon.com/console/").
```

1.2 - **Navigate to EC2:**
```text
Under the "Compute" section, click on "EC2" to open the EC2 dashboard.
Click on the "Launch Instance" button.
```

1.3 - **Choose an Amazon Machine Image (AMI):**
```text
Search for "Amazon Linux 2 AMI" and select the appropriate version.
```

1.4 - **Choose Instance Type:**
```text
Select the instance type based on your requirements. The default option is usually sufficient for testing purposes.
```

1.5 - **Configure Instance:**
```text
Configure the instance details such as the number of instances, network settings, etc. You can keep the default settings for most configurations.
```

1.6 - **Add Storage:**
```text
Specify the size and type of storage (EBS volumes) for your instance. The default settings are usually sufficient for testing purposes.
```

1.7 - **Add Tags:**
```text
(Optional) Add tags to your instance for better organization and management.
```

1.8 - **Configure Security Group:**
```text
Create a new security group or select an existing one. Make sure to allow SSH (port 22) access from your IP address or a specific range of IP addresses.
```

1.9 - **Review Instance Launch:**
```text
Review all the configurations you've made for your instance. If everything looks good, click "Launch."
```

1.10 - **Select Key Pair:**
```text
Choose an existing key pair or create a new one. This key pair is necessary to SSH into your instance.
```

1.11 - **Launch Instance:**
```text
Click "Launch Instances" to launch your EC2 instance.
```

1.12 - **Access the Instance:**
```text
Once the instance is running, you can access it via SSH using the public IP address or public DNS name provided in the EC2 dashboard, along with the private key (.pem file) associated with the selected key pair.
```

**Here is the sample configuration for Instance Launch:**

```text
AMI             : "Amazon Linux 2"
Instance Type   : "t2micro"
Region:          "N.Virginia"
VPC             : "Default VPC"
Security Group: "0.0.0.0/0-----> Port 22"
Keypair         : Create a new one as "firstkey"
```

## Part 1 - Connect with SSH for WINDOWS-"Gitbash"

# STEP_1_ Gitbash

- Open gitbash 

- Go the directory of ".pem file" and try to see "firstkey.pem" file.

```text
cd \Downloads\
ls
```
- You need to see "firstkey.pem" as a response 

# STEP_2_Connecting with Gitbash

- Go to EC2 instance pane 

- Click on "First EC2" instance

